sentences: Wood died on April 23, 2021, due to COVID-19 complications.
Victor Wood was born on February 1, 1946, in Buhi, Camarines Sur, Philippines to Sgt.
Wood's voice earned him various titles, including Jukebox King and Plaka King in the 1970s when his career bloomed.
In 1972, Wood released his third album In Despair.
Three songs on the album, namely "Jenny Jenny", "Rip It Up" and "Good Golly Miss Molly", were originally hits for Little Richard in the 1950s.
In 1974 Wood released his eleventh album, Ihilak.
In 1979, Victor covered the Indonesian version of "Anak" from the fellow Filipino original artist Freddie Aguilar.
Aside from singing, Wood was also an actor who starred in various films until 1979.
Wood ran for the Senate of the Philippines during the 2007 Philippine general election under the KBL banner, but lost.
According to his third wife, Nerissa, Wood died of complications from COVID-19 on April 23, 2021.
